      "content": "The harm principle is often misapplied when it comes to content moderation and misinformation. In reality, the government's attempts to regulate online content often rely on subjective judgments about what constitutes \"harm\" and who gets to decide what speech is acceptable. This can lead to censorship of legitimate speech, as well as the suppression of marginalized voices. Mill's original harm principle was meant to prevent physical harm, not to regulate abstract ideas or opinions.",
